## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and expert opinions, which may not cover all potential impacts of robotics on quality of life. The rapid pace of technological advancement means that new developments could alter current predictions. Additionally, the distribution of benefits from robotic technology is uncertain and could vary significantly across different regions and socioeconomic groups.